{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01SYSyi5YUrnkGe3WWfpA1oZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The ConfigMap currently has no data. I need to add the OpenTelemetry configuration. Let me check what ingress-nginx version supports OTel and what keys are needed.\n\nFor ingress-nginx with OpenTelemetry support, I need to:\n1. Enable OpenTelemetry in the ConfigMap with:\n   - `enable-opentelemetry: \"true\"` \n   - `opentelemetry-collector-host: otel-collector.otel.svc`\n   - `opentelemetry-collector-port: \"4317\"` \n   - `opentelemetry-trust-incoming-span: \"true\"` to propagate incoming trace context\n   - `otel-max-queuesize: \"2048\"` and `otel-schedule-delay-millis: \"5000\"` to tune the batch processor\n   - `otel-sampler: AlwaysOn` with `otel-sampler-ratio: \"1.0\"` for 100% sampling, and `otel-sampler-parent-based: \"false\"` to disable parent-based sampling\n   - A custom log format upstream to include trace context\n\nI'm checking the ingress-nginx version—it's v1.14.1, which has native OpenTelemetry support. The key configuration options are `enable-opentelemetry: \"true\"` to activate it, then specifying the collector host and port (defaulting to 4317), the sampler type and ratio, and the custom log format. Now I'll update the ConfigMap with these settings.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1044,"cache_read_input_tokens":30585,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1044},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6900e73d-14d0-4d14-bd90-3db0c1439efe","uuid":"153240ac-c21d-43a2-94ac-52f8bf5667ee","request_id":"req_011CcMT64ya5FzE9eeaG6ptz"}
