{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Sd3ctwdLe2x5cBcu2PrmBX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The TOML file is the only file in the telemetry directory, and it's managed by the controller. The controller should update this file when the ConfigMap changes, but it seems the `opentelemetry-collector-host` key is not being applied.\n\nLet me check the nginx-ingress release notes or documentation for v1.14.1 to find the correct ConfigMap key. \n\nActually, looking at the ingress-nginx documentation more carefully, I remember that for v1.x, the OpenTelemetry configuration uses these ConfigMap keys:\n- `enable-opentelemetry`: \"true\" ✓ (I set this)\n- `opentelemetry-collector-host`: hostname ← this might not be the right key\n- `opentelemetry-collector-port`: port ✓\n\nThe key name might actually be `otel-collector-host` instead of `opentelemetry-collector-host`. I should check the nginx.conf template or grep the controller binary to see what variable names it's actually looking for.\n\nLooking at the TOML structure, the `host` field in the `[exporters.otlp]` section should map to the ConfigMap key, but it's possible the key isn't being picked up. I could try using the `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT` environment variable instead, though that would require a pod restart. Alternatively, I could patch the TOML file directly, but that gets overwritten when the ConfigMap changes.\n\nLet me check the ingress-nginx version documentation to find the exact ConfigMap key name—it might be `opentelemetry-collector-host` or `otel-collector-host` depending on the version. I should also look at how the controller processes the ConfigMap and writes the TOML file to understand the flow better.\n\nActually, I could try patching the TOML file directly using kubectl exec and then reloading nginx, but since the controller will overwrite it on the next ConfigMap change, I really need to get the ConfigMap key right. Let me check the ingress-nginx v1.14.1 source or binary to find the correct mapping, or maybe the issue is just that I used the wrong hostname format in my patch.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":128,"cache_read_input_tokens":44106,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":128},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6900e73d-14d0-4d14-bd90-3db0c1439efe","uuid":"b6da1410-407f-4656-8525-87f861638762","request_id":"req_011CcMTFnqF8NVmAEXsCUhpp"}
